title: WATCH: Chris Petersen breaks into bag of tricks, fools USC for TD
text:
WATCH: Chris Petersen breaks into bag of tricks, fools USC for TD Chris Petersen breaks into bag of tricks, fools USC for TD 
Chris Petersen broke into his bag of tricks once again. Joe Nicholson / USA Today Oct 8, 2015 at 11:03p ET 0Shares 
Trailing 6-3 in the third quarter against USC on Thursday night, Washington head coach Chris Petersen thought it was about time to dive into his bag of tricks. 
Petersen called for a double pass, which completely fooled the Trojans defense. Huskies QB Jake Browning tossed a pass to wide receiver Marvin Hall , who in turn quickly flicked the ball to Joshua Perkins for a 27-yard touchdown.
